<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77c9ee8a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460t–4"><num value="460t–4">§ 460t–4.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is hereby authorized to be appropriated not more than $780,000 for the acquisition of land and interests in land pursuant to this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77c9ee8b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/664/s5">Pub. L. 89–664, § 5</ref>, <date date="1966-10-15">Oct. 15, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/914">80 Stat. 914</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/92/272/tI/s101/3">Pub. L. 92–272, title I, § 101(3)</ref>, <date date="1972-04-11">Apr. 11, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/120">86 Stat. 120</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id77c9ee8c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id77c9ee8d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id77c9ee8e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1972—<ref href="/us/pl/92/272">Pub. L. 92–272</ref> increased the authorization of appropriations from not more than $355,000 to not more than $780,000.</p>
</note>
</notes>
